When using GSAP in this project:

- Always use modern GSAP 3 syntax.
- In React/Next.js components, prefer the useGSAP() hook from @gsap/react.
- Register plugins through the shared helper in src/lib/gsap.ts.
- Scope animations to refs or a component root, never global selectors when a ref is possible.
- Always clean up animations on unmount. If useGSAP is not possible, use gsap.context().
- Prevent FOUC by setting initial states with gsap.set() or explicit initial hidden styles before animating in.
- Prefer gsap.timeline() for sequences instead of stacking unrelated gsap.to() calls.
- Use xPercent/yPercent for percentage-based motion.
- Respect prefers-reduced-motion and skip non-essential animation when it is enabled.
- For ScrollTrigger during development, allow markers via the shared gsapMarkers flag.
- If an animation gets messy, delete the logic and rebuild it from a single clean timeline.
